                    {"id": 3, "question": "What is the advantage of a pointed arch over a rounded arch?", "options": ["It is easier to construct", "It distributes weight more efficiently", "It uses less stone", "It is more decorative"], "answer": "It distributes weight more efficiently", "explanation": "The pointed arch distributed weight more efficiently, channeling load more directly toward the ground."},
                    {"id": 4, "question": "What is the function of flying buttresses?", "options": ["To support the roof from inside", "To decorate the exterior", "To transfer lateral forces away from the walls", "To provide ventilation"], "answer": "To transfer lateral forces away from the walls", "explanation": "Flying buttresses transferred lateral forces of the vault away from the walls to heavy piers."},
                    {"id": 5, "question": "Why could Gothic walls have large stained-glass windows?", "options": ["Glass was cheaper than stone", "The walls no longer needed to bear the full roof weight", "Windows were structurally stronger", "Romanesque buildings also had large windows"], "answer": "The walls no longer needed to bear the full roof weight", "explanation": "By externalizing support through flying buttresses, walls were freed from their load-bearing function."},
